{
    "info": {
        "name": "Smart Queue — Billing & Analytics API (Hassan Muhammad)",
        "description": "Complete test collection for Billing (Credits) and Analytics features.\n\n**How to use:**\n1. Run '1. Login' first to get a JWT token and clinicId.\n2. Run 'Get Credit Balance' to see current clinic credits.\n3. Run 'Get Available Packages' to see credit options.\n4. Run 'Create Checkout Session' to initiate a payment.\n5. Mock checkout in dev mode, or complete real Stripe payment.\n\n**Variables are auto-set by the Login script.**",
        "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
    },
    "variable": [
        { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3000/api/v1" },
        { "key": "accessToken", "value": "" },
        { "key": "clinicId", "value": "" }
    ],
    "auth": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
    },
    "item": [{
            "name": "Authentication",
            "item": [{
                "name": "1. Login (Admin/Clinic)",
                "event": [{
                    "listen": "test",
                    "script": {
                        "exec": [
                            "const res = pm.response.json();",
                            "if (res.user && res.user.accessToken) {",
                            "    pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', res.user.accessToken);",
                            "    if (res.user.clinicId) pm.collectionVariables.set('clinicId', res.user.clinicId);",
                            "    console.log('✅ Token saved. ClinicId:', res.user.clinicId);",
                            "}",
                            "pm.test('Login successful', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                        ],
                        "type": "text/javascript"
                    }
                }],
                "request": {
                    "method": "POST",
                    "url": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
                    "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                    "body": {
                        "mode": "raw",
                        "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@clinic.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\"\n}"
                    },
                    "description": "⚠️ Replace with valid admin/clinic credentials to get accessToken."
                }
            }]
        },
        {
            "name": "Billing — Credits",
            "item": [{
                    "name": "Get Credit Balance",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/credits/balance",
                        "header": [],
                        "description": "Retrieve the current clinic credit balance.\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"balance\": 500\n}\n```"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Get Available Packages",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/payments/packages",
                        "header": [],
                        "description": "Retrieve all available credit packages (no auth required).\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n[\n  { \"credits\": 50, \"price\": 99 },\n  { \"credits\": 100, \"price\": 189 },\n  { \"credits\": 200, \"price\": 349 }\n]\n```"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Billing — Payments",
            "item": [{
                    "name": "Create Checkout Session",
                    "event": [{
                        "listen": "test",
                        "script": {
                            "exec": [
                                "const res = pm.response.json();",
                                "if (res.sessionId) pm.collectionVariables.set('sessionId', res.sessionId);",
                                "pm.test('Checkout session created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                            ],
                            "type": "text/javascript"
                        }
                    }],
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/payments/checkout",
                        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"credits\": 50\n}"
                        },
                        "description": "Create a Stripe checkout session for credit purchase.\n\n**Request Body:**\n- `credits` (number): One of 50, 100, or 200\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"cs_test_...\",\n  \"checkoutUrl\": \"https://checkout.stripe.com/...\"\n}\n```\n\n**In Development:**\n- Use mock checkout mode (no real Stripe charge)\n- Manually trigger webhook event to apply credits"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Webhook: Payment Success (Test)",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/webhooks/stripe",
                        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"payment_intent.succeeded\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"object\": {\n      \"id\": \"pi_test_123\",\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"clinicId\": \"{{clinicId}}\",\n        \"credits\": 50\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}"
                        },
                        "description": "⚠️ **Test Only** — Simulates Stripe webhook event to apply credits to clinic balance.\n\nIn production, Stripe sends this automatically. For development, manually POST this to test the payment flow.\n\n**Effect:**\n- Increments clinic balance by 50 credits\n- Creates payment transaction record\n- Broadcasts socket event for real-time update"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Analytics — Metrics",
            "item": [{
                    "name": "Get Overview Stats",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/analytics/overview",
                        "header": [],
                        "description": "Retrieve high-level clinic performance metrics.\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"totalServed\": 142,\n  \"avgServiceTime\": 8.5,\n  \"currentQueueDepth\": 12,\n  \"peakHour\": 14\n}\n```"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Get Analytics Metrics (with Date Range)",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/analytics/metrics?from=2026-04-26&to=2026-05-03",
                        "header": [],
                        "description": "Retrieve detailed analytics for a date range.\n\n**Query Parameters:**\n- `from` (string): Start date (YYYY-MM-DD)\n- `to` (string): End date (YYYY-MM-DD)\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"dailyStats\": [\n    { \"date\": \"2026-04-26\", \"ticketsServed\": 18, \"avgServiceTime\": 8.2 },\n    { \"date\": \"2026-04-27\", \"ticketsServed\": 22, \"avgServiceTime\": 9.1 }\n  ],\n  \"hourlyStats\": [\n    { \"hour\": 8, \"ticketsServed\": 3 },\n    { \"hour\": 9, \"ticketsServed\": 8 },\n    { \"hour\": 14, \"ticketsServed\": 12 }\n  ],\n  \"overview\": {\n    \"totalServed\": 142,\n    \"avgServiceTime\": 8.7\n  }\n}\n```"
                    }
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}